column3: The party set out to find a suitable for the Sailors
THE GAME IS OVER, BUT YOU CAN KEEP PLAYING I GUESS.
yeah, that wasn't really a quest
The party set out with the sailors
and had a great time with them
and was seasick the entire time.
The party set out to find the logistical plans
The party was tempted to look at the documents
but managed to hold back the temptation.
and learned of some pretty unsavort things about the sailors.
The party travels with the sailor to meet the mages
and successfully made their point of contact
but the party negotiated their safe release and made their point of contact
and the party couldn't explain so paladins arrest the sailor. (DPO)
The party travels with the sailor to meet the paladins
and successfully made their point of contact
but the party negotiated the safe release and made their point of contact.
The party searched the Caves for Mana Stones
and found a rare deposit of Mana Stones.
but failed to find anything (Bad Exploration Check).
The party was charged by a herd of buffalo on the Plains
but were able to fend them off while the client conducted some tests
Then the party ran into a pack of wolves up in the Mountains
and kept them at bay long enough to capture all the wolves.
The party departed for the Mountains
and made the climb without any major incidents.
but failed (Bad Constitution Check) the climb.
The party and a bunch of suspiciously bulky Arcanists encountered a giant spider nest in the Caves
and torched every last spider and cocoon.
tried to fend them off, but had to run away as fast as they could (Bad Combat Check).
The party and the researcher snuck into the Forest past the Order outpost
and were able to "scout the area" and "collect some samples."
and had to flee because they were discovered by Order Paladins (XPO).
The party and the crew of miners proceeded carefully, but encountered a rock golem
and sucessfully pummeled it into powder.
and ran away before they were smashed to bits (Bad Combat Check).
The party tried to repel the invading Paladins
and held them off for just long enough for you to escape town.
but crumbled immediately under their superior firepower (CMB).
The party tried to negotiate with the angry Arcanists
and held them off for just long enough for you to escape town.
but the Arcanists talked circles around them (NGO) and found you in the back room anyways.
The party headed out into the forest
and mapped out the area a little!
but failed to make any progress on the map (Bad Exploration Check).
The party went searching for Mana Stones
and found some in the claws of the local wildlife
The party snuck into a Mage camp
and retrieved the "item" without a struggle
and got immediately caught (Bad Exploration Check)
The client suddenly opened fire on the boars
and the party took care of the rest.
and the party wasn't ready, so they had to flee (CMB).
The party searched for practice targets
and found a pack of wild boars
but couldn't find anything to test it on. (Bad Exploration Check)
The party engaged the rabbits using the Holy Hand Grenade
and wiped them out along with their extended family.
The party searched for a worthy foe
The party tried to negotiate a good deal with the Paladins
and the job contracts are secured. They're building the new Paladin outpost as we speak.
but could not secure all of the contracts for them. More negotiations need to be done.
Wavy-Haired Assistant: Thanks for waiting! Quest is complete. Let's see...

Great! You succeeded. Each successful Quest will return Gold, and potentially unlock more Quests. If you run out of Gold, you'll starve to death. Not right away, but after a couple of turns. Good luck out there!
The party went looking for the cat
and found him stuck in a tree.
but couldn't find hide nor hair of him (Bad Exploration Check).
The cat was scared and fought the party trying to save him,
but they managed to calm him down and retrieve him.
running off after scratching someone in the face (Bad Combat Check).
The party ran into an ankheg while doing the rounds
and couldn't take it down, so they ran all the way back to the Guild.
The party tried to calm all parties involved
and came up with a wonderful compromise.
and only made the situation worse (Bad Negotiation Check).
The party sets out to the tunnel pass
but could not find the representative.
The party sets out to the tunnel pass
but could not find the representative.
The party and the exhausted Arcanist searched the Caves for more Mana Stones
and found an even rarer deposit of Mana Stones.
but failed to find anything (Bad Exploration Check).
The party tried to negotiate a good deal with the Paladins
and the job contracts are secured. They're building the new Paladin outpost as we speak.
but could not secure all of the contracts for them. More negotiations need to be done.
The party tried to negotiate a good deal with the Paladins
and the job contracts are all secured. They're building the new Paladin outpost as we speak.
but could not secure all of the contracts for them. The Order planned to ship in experts.
and brought back an ample stash of Mana Stones.
but it went miserably (Bad Combat Check).
The party ventured into the deepest parts of the mine
and destroyed the main moth nest.
and ran away before they were eaten alive (Bad Combat Check).
